2139 /*
2140  * ======== System_printfExtend__I ========
2141  * This function processes optional extended formats of printf.
2142  *
2143  * It returns the number of characters added to the result.
2144  *
2145  * Precision (maximum string length) is not supported for %$S.
2146  *
2147  * Right-justified (which is default) minimum width is not supported
2148  * for %$L, %$S, or %$F.
2149  */
2150 xdc_Int xdc_runtime_System_printfExtend__I(xdc_Char **pbuf, xdc_CString *pfmt,
2151  xdc_VaList *pva, xdc_runtime_System_ParseData *parse)
2152 {
2153  xdc_CString fmt = *pfmt;
2154  xdc_Int res;
2155  xdc_Char c;
2156  xdc_Bool found = FALSE;
2157 
2158  /*
2159  * Create a local variable 'va' to ensure that the dereference of
2160  * pva only occurs once.
2161  */
2162  va_list va = *pva;
2163 
2164  res = 0;
2165 
2166  c = *fmt++;
2167  *pfmt = *pfmt + 1;
2168 
2169 
2170  if (c == '$') {
2171  c = *fmt++;
2172  *pfmt = *pfmt + 1;
2173 
2174  if (c == 'L') {
2175  xdc_runtime_Types_Label *lab = parse->aFlag ?
2176  (xdc_runtime_Types_Label *)xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
2177  (xdc_runtime_Types_Label *)va_arg(va, void *);
2178 
2179  /*
2180  * Call Text_putLab to write out the label, taking the precision
2181  * into account.
2182  */
2183  res = xdc_runtime_Text_putLab(lab, pbuf, parse->precis);
2184 
2185  /*
2186  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
2187  * be copied from parse.ptr.
2188  */
2189  parse->len = 0;
2190 
2191  /* Update the minimum width field. */
2192  parse->width -= res;
2193 
2194  found = TRUE;
2195  }
2196 
2197  if (c == 'F') {
2198  xdc_runtime_Types_Site site;
2199 
2200  /* Retrieve the file name string from the argument list */
2201  site.file = parse->aFlag ? (xdc_Char *) xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
2202  (xdc_Char *) va_arg(va, xdc_Char *);
2203 
2204  /* Retrieve the line number from the argument list. */
2205  site.line = parse->aFlag ? (xdc_Int) va_arg(va, xdc_IArg) :
2206  (xdc_Int) va_arg(va, xdc_Int);
2207 
2208  /*
2209  * Omit the 'mod' field, set it to 0.
2210  * '0' is a safe sentinel value - the IDs for named modules are
2211  * 0x8000 and higher, and the IDs for unnamed modules go from 0x1
2212  * to 0x7fff.
2213  */
2214  site.mod = 0;
2215 
2216  /*
2217  * Call putSite to format the file and line number.
2218  * If a precision was specified, it will be used as the maximum
2219  * string lengrth.
2220  */
2221  res = xdc_runtime_Text_putSite(&site, pbuf, parse->precis);
2222 
2223  /*
2224  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
2225  * be copied from parse.ptr.
2226  */
2227  parse->len = 0;
2228 
2229  /* Update the minimum width field */
2230  parse->width -= res;
2231 
2232  found = TRUE;
2233  }
2234 
2235  if (c == 'S') {
2236  /* Retrieve the format string from the argument list */
2237  parse->ptr = parse->aFlag ?
2238  (xdc_Char *) xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
2239  (xdc_Char *) va_arg(va, xdc_Char *);
2240 
2241  /* Update pva before passing it to doPrint. */
2242  *pva = va;
2243 
2244  /* Perform the recursive format. System_doPrint does not advance
2245  * the buffer pointer, so it has to be done explicitly.
2246  */
2247  res = xdc_runtime_System_doPrint__I(*pbuf, parse->precis,
2248  parse->ptr, pva, parse->aFlag);
2249 
2250  if (*pbuf) {
2251  *pbuf += res;
2252  }
2253 
2254  /* Update the temporary variable with any changes to *pva */
2255  va = *pva;
2256 
2257  /*
2258  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
2259  * be copied from parse.ptr
2260  */
2261  parse->len = 0;
2262 
2263  /* Update the minimum width field */
2264  parse->width -= res;
2265 
2266  /* Indicate that we were able to interpret the specifier */
2267  found = TRUE;
2268  }
2269 
2270  }
2271 
2272  if (c == 'f') {
2273  /* support arguments _after_ optional float support */
2274  if (parse->aFlag) {
2275  (void)va_arg(va, xdc_IArg);
2276  }
2277  else {
2278  (void)va_arg(va, double);
2279  }
2280  }
2281 
2282  if (found == FALSE) {
2283  /* other character (like %) copy to output */
2284  *(parse->ptr) = c;
2285  parse->len = 1;
2286  }
2287 
2288  /*
2289  * Before returning, we must update the value of pva. We use a label here
2290  * so that all return points will go through this update.
2291  * The 'goto end' is here to ensure that there is always a reference to the
2292  * label (to avoid the compiler complaining).
2293  */
2294  goto end;
2295 end:
2296  *pva = va;
2297  return (res);
2298 }

2579 /*
2580  * Header is a union to make sure that the size is a power of 2.
2581  *
2582  * On the MSP430 small model (MSP430X), size_t is 2 bytes, which makes
2583  * the size of this struct 6 bytes.
2584  */
2585 typedef union Header {
2586  struct {
2587  Ptr actualBuf;
2588  SizeT size;
2589  } header;
2590  UArg pad[2]; /* 4 words on 28L, 8 bytes on most others */
2591 } Header;
2592 
2593 
2594 
2595 /*
2596  * ======== ti_sysbios_rts_MemAlloc_alloc ========
2597  */
2598 static Void *ti_sysbios_rts_MemAlloc_alloc(SizeT size)
2599 {
2600  Header *packet;
2601  xdc_runtime_Error_Block eb;
2602 
2603  if (size == 0) {
2604  return (NULL);
2605  }
2606 
2607  xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
2608 
2609  packet = (Header *)xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL,
2610  (SizeT)(size + sizeof(Header)), 0, &eb);
2611 
2612  if (packet == NULL) {
2613  return (NULL);
2614  }
2615 
2616  packet->header.actualBuf = (Ptr)packet;
2617  packet->header.size = size + sizeof(Header);
2618 
2619  return (packet + 1);
2620 }
2621 
2622 /*
2623  * ======== malloc ========
2624  */
2625 Void ATTRIBUTE *malloc(SizeT size)
2626 {
2627  return (ti_sysbios_rts_MemAlloc_alloc(size));
2628 }
2629 
2630 /*
2631  * ======== memalign ========
2632  * mirrors the memalign() function from the TI run-time library
2633  */
2634 Void ATTRIBUTE *memalign(SizeT alignment, SizeT size)
2635 {
2636  Header *packet;
2637  Void *tmp;
2638  xdc_runtime_Error_Block eb;
2639 
2640  if (alignment < sizeof(Header)) {
2641  alignment = sizeof(Header);
2642  }
2643 
2644  /*
2645  * return NULL if size is 0, or alignment is not a power of 2
2646  */
2647  if (size == 0 || (alignment & (alignment - 1))) {
2648  return (NULL);
2649  }
2650 
2651  xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
2652 
2653  /*
2654  * Allocate 'align + size' so that we have room for the 'packet'
2655  * and can return an aligned buffer.
2656  */
2657  tmp = xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL, alignment + size, alignment, &eb);
2658 
2659  if (tmp == NULL) {
2660  return (NULL);
2661  }
2662 
2663  packet = (Header *)((char *)tmp + alignment - sizeof(Header));
2664 
2665  packet->header.actualBuf = tmp;
2666  packet->header.size = size + sizeof(Header);
2667 
2668  return (packet + 1);
2669 }
2670 
2671 /*
2672  * ======== calloc ========
2673  */
2674 Void ATTRIBUTE *calloc(SizeT nmemb, SizeT size)
2675 {
2676  SizeT nbytes;
2677  Ptr retval;
2678 
2679  nbytes = nmemb * size;
2680 
2681  /* return NULL if there's an overflow */
2682  if (nmemb && size != (nbytes / nmemb)) {
2683  return (NULL);
2684  }
2685 
2686  retval = ti_sysbios_rts_MemAlloc_alloc(nbytes);
2687  if (retval != NULL) {
2688  (Void)memset(retval, (Int)'\0', nbytes);
2689  }
2690 
2691  return (retval);
2692 }
2693 
2694 /*
2695  * ======== free ========
2696  */
2697 Void ATTRIBUTE free(Void *ptr)
2698 {
2699  Header *packet;
2700 
2701  if (ptr != NULL) {
2702  packet = ((Header *)ptr) - 1;
2703 
2704  xdc_runtime_Memory_free(NULL, (Ptr)packet->header.actualBuf,
2705  (packet->header.size +
2706  ((char*)packet - (char*)packet->header.actualBuf)));
2707  }
2708 }
2709 
2710 /*
2711  * ======== realloc ========
2712  */
2713 Void ATTRIBUTE *realloc(Void *ptr, SizeT size)
2714 {
2715  Ptr retval;
2716  Header *packet;
2717  SizeT oldSize;
2718 
2719  if (ptr == NULL) {
2720  retval = malloc(size);
2721  }
2722  else if (size == 0) {
2723  free(ptr);
2724  retval = NULL;
2725  }
2726  else {
2727  packet = (Header *)ptr - 1;
2728  retval = malloc(size);
2729  if (retval != NULL) {
2730  oldSize = packet->header.size - sizeof(Header);
2731  (Void)memcpy(retval, ptr, (size < oldSize) ? size : oldSize);
2732  free(ptr);
2733  }
2734  }
2735 
2736  return (retval);
2737 }
